Activity 1: To create a Validation rule to Course Object

1. Go to setup >> click on Object Manager >> type object name (Course) in search bar >> click on the Course object
2. Click on the validation rule >> click on New.
3. Enter the Rule name as “Course Fee Validation”.
4. Select Active
5. Insert the Error Condition Formula as:
6. Course_Fee__c <= 0 6. 
7. Enter the Error Message as “Course Fee must be greater than zero”. 
8. Select the Error location as Top of the page 
9. Click Save.

Activity 2: To create a Validation rule to Opportunity Object

Validation Rule on Start Date:

Go to setup >> click on Object Manager >> type object name (Opportunity) in search bar >> click on the Opportunity object
1. Click on the validation rule >> click on New.
2. Enter the Rule name as “Start Date Validation”.
3. Select Active
4. Insert the Error Condition Formula as: Expected_Start_Date < TODAY()
5. Enter the Error Message as “Expected Start Date cannot be in the past.”
6. Select the Error location as Top of the page
7. Click Save.

Activity 3: To create a Validation rule on Student Enrollment Object

Validation Rule on Discount Percentage:

Go to setup >> click on Object Manager >> type object name (Student Enrollment) in search bar >> click on the Student Enrollment object
1. Click on the validation rule >> click on New.
2. Enter the Rule name as “Discount Percent Validation”.
3. Select Active
4. Insert the Error Condition Formula as: Discount_Percentage__c > 50
5. Enter the Error Message as “Discount cannot be greater than 50%”.
6. Select the Error location as Top of the page
7. Click Save.
